reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars It isn't really letter size and the top isn't compatible with the bottom
reviews.reviewText: One half of the case isn’t entirely compatible with the other half of the case. The bottom is substantially larger than the top when it is fully open. I had something like this back in the 80s and the top and bottom would both accordion to the same size. With this one the bottom expands and the top doesn’t. You can either have full size, or you can have a top cover, but you can’t have both. Who thought that was a good idea?This isn’t well-suited for letter size paper. It can squeeze in there, but it can’t lay flat. The edges are forced to curl in a little because this is just a smidge too narrow. I get the feeling it was meant for A4 paper, which it looks like it will suit just fine, and then someone found out that these sell better in the US if you put “letter” in the description. They didn’t bother to find out what that meant, or if they did, they didn’t bother to test and just put the word there.I’m using this for a short-term project, and I plan to try to make do, but I don’t like it and if this goes to long term I’m replacing it.
